BIRCHWOOD POWER PARTNERS, L.P. RATE SCHEDULE NO. 1 REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE Birchwood Power Partners, L.P. ("Birchwood") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power") from its facilities to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system. This Rate Schedule sets forth Birchwood's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Power to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission").
REACTIVE POWER REVENUE REQUIREMENT
Effective on the date authorized by the Commission, the revenue requirement shall be:
Generation Facility Monthly Revenue Requirement Annual Revenue Requirement Birchwood $20,833.33 $250,000 Total Revenue Requirement $20,833.33 $250,000
